text: Erika von Heiland (born December 24, 1965) is an American badminton player, born in the Philippines. She competed in women's singles at the 1992 Summer Olympics in Barcelona, and in singles and doubles at the 1996 Summer Olympics. ==References== ==External links== * Category:1965 births Category:Living people Category:American female badminton players Category:Olympic badminton players of the United States Category:Badminton players at the 1992 Summer Olympics Category:Badminton players at the 1996 Summer Olympics Category:People from Angeles, Philippines Category:Pan American Games medalists in badminton Category:Pan American Games bronze medalists for the United States Category:Badminton players at the 1995 Pan American Games
